{
  "stem": "232.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We stayed home, and my parents sent out my brother, who looks really like a German.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He has blonde hair and blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And he went out in the street to see what's going on, came back and told us that mostly all the stores, what belongs to Jews are broken, the windows, and the merchandise was pulled out.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "People are walking in and out from the stores like it was their own.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the temples were burned and the Torah, and everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And here, a week later-- this was November 9.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And a week later, I am supposed to have my bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So the family, everybody we knew was invited to the temple to come.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And so we didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It came down a couple days later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And the week afterward, we notified our family that we will make the bar mitzvah-- we cannot make it in a temple, because the temple was burned down and broken.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "There was a little house in the back from the gabbai, the person who takes care of the temple.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He says, you can do it in my house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Tell your family to come.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And a rabbi who was already prepared for my bar mitzvah, who knew that I will have it, was ready for it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We came Saturday morning to this place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "We had about three, four people standing outside watching if they see any police, or SS, or Nazis coming, to warn us so that we can escape from the behind in the backyard.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to describe the temple-- it was a room.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In one corner were the burnt Torah scrolls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were laying on the floo-- [SOBBING] I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were laying on the floor, covered.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] I did my [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
